LEGS. Without spines, with curved hairs on metatarsi, with vertical hairs in higher than usual density in one retrolatero-dorsal row on each tibia; retrolateral trichobothrium on tibia 1 at 2%; prolateral trichobothrium absent on tibia 1, present on other tibiae. Tarsus 1 with ~30 pseudosegments, distally distinct. Tarsus 4 comb-hairs with very dense tines (
Fig. 32
).
